<div class="indented"><a id="comment-9705"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/two-sources-energy-and-using-heat#comment-9705" class="active">Overhead power</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Sat, 2009-05-09 07:10.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Cars may need two wires (like a trolley bus) which is more complex, and has many other issues.  Plus you can only go where the wires are &#8212; or you need batteries or an engine anyway.    You get wires ruining the look of the streets, unless one can design a safe ground based power system, which is hard to do to work in the rain and deliver all that current.</p>

<p>Lots of power means high voltage, and fire risks.</p>
</div>
